
Tipps and tools for running Xilinx Vivado on Ubuntu (Kubuntu) 2014.04
=====================================================================

1. before installing run "sudo dpkg-reconfigure dash" and choose not to
use dash as (/bin/sh). After that /bin/sh should be a symlink to "bash".

2. when running Kubuntu (KDE): Change "System Settings > Application
Appearance > GTK > GTK2" from "oxygen-gtk" to "Raleigh" [1].

3. install Vivado. select full install ("System Edition" + SDK) and
install in the default locations:

	/opt/Xilinx/Vivado/{version}/
	/opt/Xilinx/Vivado_HLS/{version}/
	/opt/Xilinx/SDK/{version}/

4. change the "web_command" and "pdf_command" settings in "wrapper.sh"
to reflect your choices and run "sudo bash install.sh {version}".

5. run "/opt/Xilinx/DocNav/docnav", open the Settings Dialog, and set
"Preferences > PDF Viewer Path" to "/opt/Xilinx/Vivado/{version}/bin/acroread".

[1] http://forums.xilinx.com/t5/High-Level-Synthesis-HLS/Vivado-HLS-crashes-on-Kubuntu-14-04-solved/td-p/472112

